<div class="titles">
  <h2>The Moment I Realized I Married the White Rabbit</h2>
  <h3>by Beverly Frydman</h3>
</div>
<!-- content -->
<div class="border">
 <p>
          
Falling towards London <br />
747 drops hard then settles <br />
unlike my stomach wrestling <br />
microwaved chicken curry
<br /><br />
Overhead compartment opens<br />
my hobo handbag empties tampons<br />
a hairbrush, just in case panties<br />
red Channel lipstick in a black lacquer case
<br /><br />
My private life lands on loafers<br />
belonging to my beloved<br />
he jiggles his leg in his aisle seat<br />
picks up my stuff, checks his watch<br />
<br /><br />
We land with a thud and applause<br />
thank god we survived<br />
every soul on board unbuckles<br />
preparing to rush for the exit
<br /><br />
My new husband grabs his backpack<br />
slings my purse over his shoulder<br />
scampers into the aisle crying<br />
we’re late we’re late<br /><br />
  </p>
  
</div>

